"script": "A retired teacher climbed into a wooden barrel and let it tumble straight over Niagara Falls. The crowd gasped as it vanished into the roaring mist below. Then, against all odds, the barrel bobbed back up, and she crawled out alive, the first person ever to survive the plunge. Reporters called her fearless. But here's the dark part. Years later, walking down an ordinary street, she slipped on a single orange peel and shattered her hip. And that simple fall, not the waterfall, is what eventually killed her. The Falls couldn't do it, but a sidewalk did.",
